AMD recently unveiled its new Ryzen 2000 desktop processors, which are now available for pre-order in South Africa. The new chips offer increased efficiency paired with high core counts, making them ideal for multi-threaded applications. The Ryzen 2000 desktop lineup comprises two Ryzen 5 processors and two Ryzen 7 chips, which sport six and eight cores respectively. AMD also previously released two Ryzen 2000 processors with integrated graphics, although their core count is limited compared to the new chips. According to local product listings, the Ryzen 2000 processors will be available from 19 April 2018. Local prices for AMDâ€™s Ryzen 2000 range are below. Rebel Tech Wootware Evetech